rfweber@bcstec.ca.boeing.com (Robert F. Weber) writes:

>00011=1
>00101=2
>00110=3
>01001=4
>01010=5
>01100=6
>10001=7
>10010=8
>10100=9
>11000=0

This is the 2 of 5 code, of which there are exactly 10.
The weights of the bits (except for the 0 code) are 7, 4, 2, 1, parity.

Note that all single-bit errors can be detected.  A check digit
therefore provides one bit of error correction.

